cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.MM

This paper involves machine learning techniques for evaluating the impact of probabilistically-constructed digital identity data in the context of lookalike-targeted campaigns. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational advertising (cs.CR) as it deals with user modeling and ad targeting. Additionally, it involves social and information networks (cs.SI) as it deals with user identities and their relationships. Finally, it involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with mobile ad identifiers and associated metadata.
